(853, 1, '2016-03-02 17:02:00', '2016-03-02 17:02:00', 'The Ratapani Tiger Reserve, located in the Raisen district of Madhya Pradesh, in Vindhya Range in central India, is one of the finest teak forests in the state and is less than 50 km. away from the capital Bhopal.\n\nIt has been a wildlife sanctuary since 1976. As of March 2013, in principle approval by the National Tiger Conservation Authority (NTCA) has been granted for upgrading it to a status of tiger reserve. It will become a tiger reserve by the notification of the Government of Madhya Pradesh.[3] Its close proximity to the capital and its relatively untouched forests makes it a promising attraction for tourists and the Madhya Pradesh tourism board plans to make it a wildlife destination in the near future. The reserve is rich in flora and fauna and a wide variety of birds, mammals and reptiles call it their home.\n', 'Ratapani Tiger Reserve', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '810-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-03-02 17:02:00', '2016-03-02 17:02:00', '', 810, 'http://www.mpinformation.com/810-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(854, 1, '2016-03-02 17:12:11', '2016-03-02 17:12:11', '<h3>About Ratapani Tiger Reserve</h3>\r\nThe Ratapani Tiger Reserve, located in the Raisen district of Madhya Pradesh, in Vindhya Range in central India, is one of the finest teak forests in the state and is less than 50 km. away from the capital Bhopal.\r\n\r\nIt has been a wildlife sanctuary since 1976. As of March 2013, in principle approval by the National Tiger Conservation Authority (NTCA) has been granted for upgrading it to a status of tiger reserve. It will become a tiger reserve by the notification of the Government of Madhya Pradesh.[3] Its close proximity to the capital and its relatively untouched forests makes it a promising attraction for tourists and the Madhya Pradesh tourism board plans to make it a wildlife destination in the near future. The reserve is rich in flora and fauna and a wide variety of birds, mammals and reptiles call it their home.\r\n<h3>History</h3>\r\nRatapani forest was declared as wildlife sanctuary in year 1976. Since then, it retained this status till year 2013 when National Tiger Conservation Authority (NTCA) granted the approval to upgrade this wildlife sanctuary to tiger reserve. State government of Madhya Pradesh is working on it to notify the tiger reserve area, create core-buffer zones for reserve and develop it.\r\n<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n<tbody><tr>\r\n<td width="12%"><strong>By Air</strong></td>\r\n<td width="88%">Bhopal Airport is the nearest one which is located at the distance of 70 km from the city.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>By Train</strong></td>\r\n<td>Bhopal Railway Station is the nearest station to reach the city.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>By Road</strong></td>\r\n<td>There are several tourist and private buses from Bhopal	(60 Km), Pachmarhi (160 Km), Sanchi (120 km), Indore (260 km), and Jabalpur (280 km), which are well connected to Ratapani Tiger Reserve.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody></table>